# Learning Support Provider Directory - Local Setup Package

## Quick Start

1. **Create a new directory and navigate to it:**
   ```bash
   mkdir learning-support-directory
   cd learning-support-directory
   ```

2. **Initialize package.json:**
   ```bash
   npm init -y
   ```

3. **Install dependencies:**
   ```bash
   npm install express @tanstack/react-query wouter react react-dom @types/react @types/react-dom @types/node @types/express typescript tsx vite @vitejs/plugin-react tailwindcss autoprefixer postcss
   ```

4. **Install UI components:**
   ```bash
   npm install lucide-react class-variance-authority clsx tailwind-merge @radix-ui/react-slot @radix-ui/react-toast @radix-ui/react-tooltip @radix-ui/react-select @radix-ui/react-alert-dialog framer-motion
   ```

5. **Copy all the files from the attached code structure**

6. **Run the application:**
   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:5000`

